    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Renggeria comans are its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities. The plant's antimicrobial properties contribute to its wound healing and infection prevention capabilities. Its antiseptic and antifungal properties also play a crucial role in its ability to prevent infections and promote tissue repair. The plant's bioactive compounds, including flavonoids, saponins, and volatile oils, are primarily responsible for its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial properties. These compounds work together to exhibit the plant's anti-ulcer and immunomodulatory effects, making it a valuable resource for traditional medicine.",
