    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Renggeria comans are flavonoids, terpenes, and phenolic acids, which have been identified as responsible for its medicinal properties. Flavonoids present in the plant exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, contributing to its potential in reducing oxidative stress and inflammation. Terpenes, specifically monoterpenes and sesquiterpenes, have been found to possess antimicrobial and antifungal properties, making the plant effective against various microbial infections. Phenolic acids, including gallic acid and ellagic acid, have been reported to display antioxidant and anti-cancer activities, potentially contributing to the plant's anti-proliferative effects. These constituents work synergistically to provide the plant's healing properties, making Renggeria comans a valuable resource for traditional medicine.",
