    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Renggeria comans are derived from its leaves and stems, used for medicinal purposes. A tea is prepared by infusing the leaves and stems in hot water to treat fever, colds, and respiratory issues. An infusion is made by steeping the leaves and stems in cold water to relieve digestive issues and as a diuretic. A tincture is prepared through the solvent extraction of the plant's bioactive compounds, used for its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. A decoction or salve can be prepared to treat skin irritations and wounds due to the presence of saponins and other compounds in the plant.",
